JOHANNESBURG - The so-called Samurai killer of Krugersdorp, Morne Harmse, has been released on parole. But eNCA can reveal that questions have been raised about his mental state and the decision to grant him early release. Correctional Services has defended the decision, saying they are confident Harmse is not a danger to society. * eNCA's Barry Bateman has more on this exclusive story. eNCA's Barry Bateman has the details. #DStv403 #eNCA.